This plugin allows to block access to specified plugins or plugin area parts for admin panel selected users.

It&#039;s great addon when you using Multi User plugin that hides plugin tab but not block entering plugin configurations by entering URL.

&lt;h4&gt;How to use&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enter usernames to apply permission check&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Select rule, allow only or deny&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Add queries to check. For example adding: &#039;id=i18n_specialpages&amp;create&#039; query and selecting &#039;allow only&#039; rule will allow entering only into &#039;Create New Special Page&#039; option menu form Pages tab. &lt;br&gt;
This plugin will allow for access only when all specified params and it&#039;s values from entered query are matched in URL query when GS executing &#039;load.php&#039; file for loading plugin. 
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


