GroupDocs.Viewer is a universal document viewer that lets you display PDF, Microsoft Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Visio and other types of documents on your GetSimple website. This particular plugin integrates the downloadable &lt;a href=&quot;http://groupdocs.com/java/document-viewer-library&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Java version of the viewer&lt;/a&gt;.

&lt;h4&gt;Display PDF, Word, Excel &amp; More&lt;/h4&gt;
GroupDocs.Viewer supports over 50 types of popular document and image file formats. Using the viewer, you can embed and display any of the following types of files on your GetSimple website:

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Portable Document Format: PDF&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Microsoft Word: DOC, DOCX, DOCM, DOT, DOTX, DOTM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Microsoft Excel: XLS, XLSX, XLSM, XLSB, XML&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Microsoft PowerPoint: PPT, PPTX&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Microsoft Outlook: MSG, EML&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Microsoft Project: MPP, MPT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Microsoft Visio: VSD, VDX, VSS, VSX, VST, VTX, VSDX, VDW&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;OpenDocument Formats: ODT, OTT, ODS, ODP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plain Text File: TXT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rich Text Format: RTF&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comma-Separated Values: CSV&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HyperText Markup Language: HTM, HTML, MHT, MHTML&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;XML Paper Specification: XPS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AutoCAD Drawing File Format: DXF&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Image files: BMP, GIF, JPG, PNG, TIFF&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Electronic publication: EPUB&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h4&gt;Provide Unmatched User Experience&lt;/h4&gt;
GroupDocs.Viewer for Java doesn&rsquo;t require any installation on the client side. It allows users to view documents from any popular web-browser, including IE8+, Chrome, Opera, FireFox, Safari5+ and their mobile versions. There is no need to install Adobe Acrobat Reader to view PDF documents, for example.

The viewer also comes with a web-interface designed to make it easy to navigate large documents in a browser. You can embed the UI right into web-pages on your website. The UI allows your website visitors to:

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Turn document pages like slides&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preview/navigate pages with thumbnails&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fit to width/height/visible or zoom in/out of a document&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Search for text with the document, select and copy text to the clipboard&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Download and print documents (these options can be restricted/disabled)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h4&gt;High-Fidelity Fonts Rendering&lt;/h4&gt;
GroupDocs.Viewer for Java can both, rasterize documents, or convert them to pure HTML, CSS and SVG. When documents are rasterized, the viewer extracts texts and then renders them in a separate layer over the background images. Both modes provide high-fidelity text rendering, so that fonts always look sharp and clear.

