&lt;pre&gt;
`
    &lt;div class=&quot;menuitem_lvl_1&quot;&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;menuitem_lvl_1&quot;&gt;...
        &lt;div class=&quot;menuitem_lvl_2 current active&quot;&gt;...
            &lt;div class=&quot;menuitem_lvl_3&quot;&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;menuitem_lvl_3&quot;&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;menuitem_lvl_1&quot;&gt;...&lt;/div&gt;
`
&lt;/pre&gt;

Blocking user access to the site by the IP address. 

In the &quot;settings&quot; section the &quot;Blocking by IP address&quot;

It is enough to specify the ip address of the user, the reason for the blocking and the end date and the specified user will be blocked.

If you do not specify the end date of the lock, the user will be blocked until you manually delete his ip from the database.

When the end date of the lock comes, the user will be able to automatically access the site, his ip address will be deleted from the database.

